<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-10-03T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-10-03T12:00:00-05:00" n="62" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d62">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 European Advisory
                            Commission/10–344: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Winant</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-10-03T18:00:00+01:00">October 3,
                                    1944—6 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received October 3—4:44 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>8273. Department’s 8037, October 2, 7 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d62fn1">See
                                footnote 98, <ref target="#pg_91">p. 91</ref>.</note> With reference
                            to the request of the French Committee that its representative be
                            admitted to sit on the European Advisory Commission I am glad to have
                            your comment. Although this matter has never been officially before the
                            EAC and might be favored by the British, I am certain that the Russians
                            would be violently against it and I believe it would be a mistake to
                            introduce any other national element into the Commission until the
                            military phase is established, following the surrender of Germany. The
                            essential task in the EAC at the present time is to reach agreed
                            conclusion on a tripartite basis.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>